65static const SymbolInfo* s_symbols = PROD_SYMBOLS;
66static ZXING_IF_NOT_TEST(const) size_t s_symbolCount = Size(PROD_SYMBOLS);
67
68#if ZXING_BUILD_FOR_TEST
69
70ZXING_EXPORT_TEST_ONLY
71void OverrideSymbolSet(const SymbolInfo* symbols, size_t count)
72{
73 s_symbols = symbols;
74 s_symbolCount = count;
75}
76
77ZXING_EXPORT_TEST_ONLY
78void UseDefaultSymbolSet()
79{
80 s_symbols = PROD_SYMBOLS;
81 s_symbolCount = Size(PROD_SYMBOLS);
82}
83
84#endif // ZXING_BUILD_FOR_TEST

86const SymbolInfo *
87SymbolInfo::Lookup(int dataCodewords)
88{
89 return Lookup(dataCodewords, SymbolShape::NONE);
90}
91
92const SymbolInfo *
93SymbolInfo::Lookup(int dataCodewords, SymbolShape shape)
94{
95 return Lookup(dataCodewords, shape, -1, -1, -1, -1);
96}
97
98const SymbolInfo *
99SymbolInfo::Lookup(int dataCodewords, bool allowRectangular)
100{
101 return Lookup(dataCodewords, allowRectangular ? SymbolShape::NONE : SymbolShape::SQUARE, -1, -1, -1, -1);
102}
103
104const SymbolInfo *
105SymbolInfo::Lookup(int dataCodewords, SymbolShape shape, int minWidth, int minHeight, int maxWidth, int maxHeight)
106{
107 for (size_t i = 0; i < s_symbolCount; ++i) {
108 auto& symbol = s_symbols[i];
109 if (shape == SymbolShape::SQUARE && symbol._rectangular) {
110 continue;
111 }
112 if (shape == SymbolShape::RECTANGLE && !symbol._rectangular) {
113 continue;
114 }
115 if (minWidth >= 0 && minHeight >= 0 && (symbol.symbolWidth() < minWidth || symbol.symbolHeight() < minHeight)) {
116 continue;
117 }
118 if (maxWidth >= 0 && maxHeight >= 0 && (symbol.symbolWidth() > maxWidth || symbol.symbolHeight() > maxHeight)) {
119 continue;
120 }
121 if (dataCodewords <= symbol._dataCapacity) {
122 return &symbol;
123 }
124 }
125 return nullptr;
126}
127
128int
129SymbolInfo::horizontalDataRegions() const
130{
131 switch (_dataRegions) {
132 case 1:
133 return 1;
134 case 2:
135 return 2;
136 case 4:
137 return 2;
138 case 16:
139 return 4;
140 case 36:
141 return 6;
142 default:
143 throw std::out_of_range("Cannot handle this number of data regions");
144 }
145}
146
147int
148SymbolInfo::verticalDataRegions() const {
149 switch (_dataRegions) {
150 case 1:
151 return 1;
152 case 2:
153 return 1;
154 case 4:
155 return 2;
156 case 16:
157 return 4;
158 case 36:
159 return 6;
160 default:
161 throw std::out_of_range("Cannot handle this number of data regions");
162 }
163}
